WEBVTT

00:04.195 --> 00:06.757
So this whole leap year thing
doesn't freak you out at all?

00:06.781 --> 00:08.291
Why would it?

00:08.867 --> 00:10.428
I don't know. Just the idea

00:10.452 --> 00:13.472
that's there's this... this
day that doesn't even exist.

00:13.496 --> 00:14.807
Like a phantom day.

00:14.831 --> 00:16.350
But it's just science, Bailey.

00:16.373 --> 00:17.977
I mean if we didn't add the day,

00:18.001 --> 00:20.771
eventually, you know, we'd end
up with sun and snow in June.

00:20.795 --> 00:22.732
Well, see, now,
that's exactly it.

00:22.756 --> 00:24.692
That's exactly what
freaks me out about it.

00:24.716 --> 00:26.142
That that could happen.

00:27.469 --> 00:28.613
What are you doing?

00:28.637 --> 00:30.489
I'm having an existential
crisis out here,

00:30.513 --> 00:32.700
and you're, like,
rearranging my clothes.

00:32.723 --> 00:33.868
I am not.

00:33.892 --> 00:34.827
Then what are you doing?

00:34.851 --> 00:36.277
It's a surprise.

00:36.311 --> 00:38.488
Ah! Brainstorm.

00:38.647 --> 00:40.207
What if we throw a
leap year party.

00:40.231 --> 00:41.459
If you're surrounded by friends,

00:41.483 --> 00:43.242
maybe it'll help you
through the trauma.

00:43.610 --> 00:44.911
Maybe.

00:47.030 --> 00:48.706
Okay. Ready?

00:49.157 --> 00:50.833
Ta-da!

00:52.619 --> 00:54.087
What do you think?

01:01.503 --> 01:02.855
Oh. Oh, God.

01:02.879 --> 01:03.856
You know, I can take it back.

01:03.880 --> 01:05.441
No! Don't...

01:05.465 --> 01:07.526
I mean... I mean...

01:07.550 --> 01:08.861
no.

01:08.885 --> 01:09.862
Are you sure?

01:09.886 --> 01:12.188
You know, because it's not
really my normal style.

01:13.139 --> 01:15.534
Maybe it's a new me emerging.

01:15.558 --> 01:18.528
Yeah, well... emerge over here.

01:24.526 --> 01:26.754
So... this leap
year party thing,

01:26.778 --> 01:28.162
what do you say?

01:28.363 --> 01:29.872
Yes...

01:30.281 --> 01:32.583
to absolutely anything.

01:38.164 --> 01:39.642
Well, here.

01:39.666 --> 01:41.268
You have a history
test on Monday.

01:41.292 --> 01:43.302
So I figured you
might want to...

01:46.131 --> 01:49.235
I also brought you a
note from Nina, um...

01:49.259 --> 01:50.653
the <i>Grant High Spectator,</i>

01:50.677 --> 01:53.229
and a new class
president ballot.

02:00.145 --> 02:01.863
Lots of people are
asking about you.

02:03.690 --> 02:05.167
Asking what?

02:05.191 --> 02:06.784
How you are?

02:07.152 --> 02:08.995
what's wrong, when
you're gonna be back.

02:09.571 --> 02:10.631
And what do you tell them?

02:10.655 --> 02:12.591
I tell 'em you're okay,

02:12.615 --> 02:14.135
you had a stomach virus,

02:14.159 --> 02:16.127
and you're gonna be
back really soon.

02:18.288 --> 02:19.630
Are you?

02:20.248 --> 02:22.258
Gonna be back soon?

02:23.126 --> 02:24.510
I don't know.

02:25.086 --> 02:26.387
Oh.

02:28.590 --> 02:30.475
Because I was thinking...

02:31.801 --> 02:33.821
maybe if you did come back,

02:33.845 --> 02:37.190
uh, got back into your routine,

02:37.390 --> 02:39.776
you might start feeling
like your old self again.

02:40.727 --> 02:43.738
And maybe we'd start
feeling like us again.

02:44.856 --> 02:47.075
Maybe it's as easy as that.

02:48.193 --> 02:49.420
Yeah...

02:49.444 --> 02:50.787
maybe.

